ARGUMENT.

In traversing Garioch and its snowy tracts‚ beware of the waters of the Gadie; taste them not, touch them not, look to them not, but shade your eyes with both your palms. Gadie is known to all the world, yea‚ to the under-world as well. Not that it turns to stone or does other harmful things. It infects with amorous desire: such as appeared in the dames of fable old. There is some virus in its waters. The stream is believed to spring from Tyrian Gades, and, like Alpheus, finds its way northward underneath the sea. Avoid its waterS. A chaste Penelope will, under its influence, depart a Thais, and Diana herself will follow Dione.
